Jay Jakosky (matrix@kaiwan.com) wrote:
:         We seem so happy that RIPEM/SIG is now a commodity and therefore
: a legal implementation of cryptoware.  But don't forget it's single key
: algorithm is DES.  

RIPEM/SIG is signature-only.  It uses MD5 for the message
digest, and RSA to encrypt the message digest.  There is
no data encryption--that is why RIPEM/SIG got approved for export.
/mrr
